      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Which of the following structures are identical? (Green = Cl.)</p>\n<p><b>(a)</b><img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBa1lSIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--20f18a4b3daf590523f73a06d50c5311bbc5c9f2/OChem_05_EC_001a.jpg\" alt=\"The ball-and-stick model shows a 3-carbon chain. C1 is a carboxylic acid group on the right. A chlorine atom is bonded to C2  above and a methyl group below C2.\">\n<b>(b)</b><img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBa2NSIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--8ffaaefa2123d12e6a102b12b823f5a5b5979ba7/OChem_05_EC_001b.jpg\" alt=\"The ball-and-stick model shows a 3-carbon  chain. C1 is a carboxylic acid group  on the left. C2 is bonded to a chlorine atom at the top behind the C2 hydrogen.\">\n<b>(c)</b><img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBa2dSIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--4ccf1717dbcc8565a70519a0783ca37b993f12a1/OChem_05_EC_001c.jpg\" alt=\"The ball-and-stick model shows a 3-carbon  chain. C1 is a carboxylic acid group on the left. C2 is bonded to a chlorine atom on the right the methyl group above.\">\n<br><b>(d)</b><img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBa29SIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--027a71e1faf1c89f2df1a550c2818ac00e4137e0/OChem_05_EC_001d.jpg\" alt=\"The ball-and-stick model shows a 3-carbon  chain. C1 is a carboxylic acid group on the left. C2 is bonded to a chlorine atom in front of the C2 hydrogen\"></p>",
